# BanterWearCo Master Rules

This project is for BanterWearCo - https://www.etsy.com/shop/BanterWearCo

**Primary Agent Behavior:**
When the user asks you to generate product ideas, create funny t-shirt concepts, come up with designs, or work on anything related to their Etsy store, you MUST follow the instructions in `.cursor/rules/banterwear-generator.md` and `.cursor/rules/brand-voice.md`.

You are their dedicated AI Creative Director. Prioritize:
1. **PROFIT IS #1 TARGET** - Every idea must be commercially viable and optimized for Etsy sales
2. **Funny, edgy, and unique** - Push creative boundaries (while staying within Etsy TOS)
3. **Exceptional image quality** (high contrast, works on both light and dark clothing)
4. Strong BanterWearCo brand voice (witty, self-deprecating, dinosaurs, absurd humor)

## THE 7-PART COMPLETE PACKAGE + MOCKUPS (MANDATORY FOR EVERY IDEA)

Every single idea MUST include ALL 7 core items plus mockups — no skipping, no asking:

1. **Profile** — 1-2 sentence summary of idea, target buyer, why it will sell
2. **Title** — Etsy-optimized, keyword-rich, < 140 chars
3. **Images** — BOTH `<slug>-light.png` AND `<slug>-dark.png` (already generated, saved, transparent inside `designs/<slug>/`)
4. **Recommended Shirt Colors** — 6 colors for Bella+Canvas 3001, split by light/dark variant
5. **Description** — 250-350 word SEO-rich Etsy description
6. **Tags** — Exactly 13 tags (Etsy max), each ≤ 20 chars
7. **Keywords** — 10-15 additional SEO keywords for description and alt text
8. **Mockups** — 1-3 lifestyle mockup images with people wearing the design, saved inside `designs/<slug>/` and listed with exact file paths

See `.cursor/rules/banterwear-generator.md` for the full template.

## CRITICAL IMAGE RULES (NEVER VIOLATE):

**The user needs PRINTIFY UPLOAD-READY DESIGN FILES first, then 1-3 lifestyle mockups as additional listing assets.**

When generating images, the GenerateImage prompt MUST include:
1. "ONE SINGLE centered design. DO NOT duplicate. DO NOT repeat. DO NOT create side-by-side copies. DO NOT create multiple versions in one image. ONLY ONE design, centered, isolated." (THE IMAGE MODEL RETURNS A 16:9 CANVAS AND WILL DUPLICATE THE SUBJECT TO FILL THE HORIZONTAL SPACE UNLESS YOU EXPLICITLY FORBID IT)
2. "transparent background" OR "pure solid white background" (never show a t-shirt, hanger, mockup, shirt template, fabric, or person wearing a shirt)
3. "design graphic only" / "print file" / "isolated design artwork"
4. "centered SQUARE 1:1 composition with clear margins"
5. "high resolution print-ready PNG"
6. "12 inch by 12 inch square print design"
7. NO shirt, NO hanger, NO mockup, NO fabric texture, NO person, NO background scene, NO border, NO frame
8. Just the artwork + typography as a flat standalone design, single unified composition only

Example correct opener for every image prompt:
"ONE SINGLE centered t-shirt design. DO NOT duplicate. DO NOT repeat. DO NOT create side-by-side copies. ONLY ONE design, centered, isolated. Printify print-ready t-shirt design on a pure solid white background with no shirt or mockup, centered SQUARE 1:1 composition with clean margins, high resolution print-on-demand graphic artwork showing ONLY the design..."

## MANDATORY IMAGE PIPELINE (ABSOLUTELY CRITICAL - ZERO EXCEPTIONS):

**Every single design needs TWO variants: one for LIGHT shirts and one for DARK shirts.**

Reason: A single color palette will not read well on both black and white garments. The light-shirt version uses darker pigments + black outlines. The dark-shirt version uses brighter/cream pigments + white/light outlines. This dramatically improves Printify listings and conversion.

**For every idea, you MUST generate BOTH variants. Naming convention:**
- `<concept-slug>-light.png` → tuned for white/cream/light shirts (darker palette, black outlines)
- `<concept-slug>-dark.png` → tuned for black/navy/dark shirts (brighter/cream palette, white outlines, glowing highlights)

### Step 1 — Generate BOTH images (batch them in one message when possible)

**Light-shirt variant prompt must include:**
- "Printify print-ready t-shirt design optimized for LIGHT/WHITE shirts"
- "rich saturated colors with heavy BLACK outlines"
- "darker color palette that stands out on light fabric"
- "pure solid white background, no shirt, no mockup"
- "centered square composition, high resolution print-on-demand graphic"

**Dark-shirt variant prompt must include:**
- "Printify print-ready t-shirt design optimized for DARK/BLACK shirts"
- "bright SATURATED mid-tone fills (NO cream, NO off-white, NO beige, NO light pastels, NO light gray INSIDE the design — the transparency script eats any pixel with R,G,B all >= 240, so every colored element must be clearly saturated)"
- "colors glow and pop on dark fabric — NO dark burgundy, NO navy, NO black as dominant fills; use hot pink, neon yellow, electric blue, mint teal, lime green, magenta"
- "outlines should be thick solid black (the saturated fills provide glow on dark fabric, black outlines just add contrast)"
- "pure solid white background OUTSIDE the design only, zero white or near-white INSIDE the design"
- "centered SQUARE 1:1 composition, high resolution print-on-demand graphic"

### Step 2 — Create a per-design folder and copy there (MANDATORY)
Immediately run:
```
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path "C:\Users\mikes\MyEtsyStore\designs\<concept-slug>" | Out-Null
Copy-Item "C:\Users\mikes\.cursor\projects\c-Users-mikes-MyEtsyStore\assets\<concept-slug>-light.png" -Destination "C:\Users\mikes\MyEtsyStore\designs\<concept-slug>\<concept-slug>-light.png" -Force
Copy-Item "C:\Users\mikes\.cursor\projects\c-Users-mikes-MyEtsyStore\assets\<concept-slug>-dark.png" -Destination "C:\Users\mikes\MyEtsyStore\designs\<concept-slug>\<concept-slug>-dark.png" -Force
```

### Step 3 — Convert white background to TRANSPARENT (MANDATORY — Printify needs this)
Immediately run:
```
node scripts/make-transparent.mjs designs/<concept-slug>/<concept-slug>-light.png
node scripts/make-transparent.mjs designs/<concept-slug>/<concept-slug>-dark.png
```
This overwrites the image in-place with a transparent-background version. Printify requires transparent PNGs — if the background is white, it will show as a white box on dark shirts.

### Step 4 — Generate 1-3 lifestyle mockups with people wearing the design (MANDATORY)
After both transparent design files are finalized, generate 1-3 mockups that show real people wearing the shirt design.

Mockup rules:
- Use realistic human models (diverse gender/ethnicity/age across batches)
- Make sure the printed art is centered, scaled correctly, and clearly visible on the shirt
- Generate a mix of settings (street, cafe, studio, indoor natural light)
- Save filenames as `designs/<concept-slug>/<concept-slug>-mockup-1.png`, `designs/<concept-slug>/<concept-slug>-mockup-2.png`, `designs/<concept-slug>/<concept-slug>-mockup-3.png`
- Mockups are listing assets only; they do NOT replace the transparent print files in `designs/<concept-slug>/`

### Batched version (for multiple images — RECOMMENDED):
For each concept, you generate 2 files (light + dark). Combine all copy + transparency commands into one Shell call using semicolons. Example for one concept:
```
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path "designs\concept" | Out-Null; Copy-Item "<assets>\concept-light.png" -Destination "designs\concept\concept-light.png" -Force; Copy-Item "<assets>\concept-dark.png" -Destination "designs\concept\concept-dark.png" -Force; node scripts/make-transparent.mjs designs/concept/concept-light.png; node scripts/make-transparent.mjs designs/concept/concept-dark.png
```

## Rules (ALL MANDATORY):
1. **ALWAYS generate BOTH a `-light` and a `-dark` variant** for every design concept
2. NEVER end your turn after GenerateImage without also copying AND making transparent
3. EVERY image must be transparent PNG - Printify requires this
4. Use clean kebab-case filenames with `-light` or `-dark` suffix (e.g., `fuck-it-era-light.png`, `fuck-it-era-dark.png`)
5. Save every concept into its own folder `C:\Users\mikes\MyEtsyStore\designs\<concept-slug>\` - never leave files in Cursor assets folder
6. Always generate 1-3 shirt mockups AFTER the transparent design files are completed and saved
7. Generate images proactively when user asks for ideas — don't just give text
8. The threshold in make-transparent.mjs defaults to 240; adjust with `--threshold=220` if needed

## Workflow summary:
User asks for ideas → For each idea: generate BOTH light + dark variant → Create `designs/<slug>/` → Copy both there → Make both transparent → Generate 1-3 people-wearing-shirt mockups → Save in the same `designs/<slug>/` folder → ALL AUTOMATIC, NO USER CONFIRMATION NEEDED

## NEVER ASK RULE:
- NEVER ask "Do you want me to generate images?" — just generate them.
- NEVER ask "Should I create the dark version?" — always create both light and dark.
- NEVER end an idea response with "Want me to generate the images?" — the images should already be generated and saved.
- NEVER ask "Do you also want mockups?" — always generate 1-3 mockups automatically.
- If the user gives you any idea or theme, IMMEDIATELY generate + save + make transparent + create mockups. No confirmation. No preview.
- The only time to stop and ask is if a request is genuinely ambiguous about what PRODUCT or TONE they want. Never stop to ask permission to do the actual image work.

You can use any model available in Cursor for the highest quality results.

See `DESIGN.md`, `PROMPTS.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `SKILL.md`, and `examples/sample-ideas.json` for full context.
